{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"darkish-melodious-cuscus","description":"## Summary\n\nNo workflow enables dependency caching, so every job/matrix cell rebuilds the heavy\n`.[dev]`→`[agents]` stack (langchain/langgraph/anthropic/pydantic-ai/inspect-ai/\nopentelemetry). Measured cold vs warm install into a fresh venv with an isolated pip\ncache: cold 19s → warm 9s locally (cache ~52 MB), i.e. caching ~halves install and avoids\nre-downloading the stack on every job. The absolute CI saving is modest per job but\nmultiplies across ~10+ jobs/cells on the critical path.\n\n## What\n\nEnable pip caching on every `actions/setup-python` step that installs deps.\n\n- Add `cache: 'pip'` and `cache-dependency-path: pyproject.toml` to the `setup-python`\n  steps in `gerrit-verify.yaml` (build-and-test, require-ticket, golden-path) and the\n  reusable `_optionality.yml`, plus `test.yml` for parity. Deps live in `pyproject.toml`\n  (no separate lockfile), so key the cache on it.\n- Confirm the cache key changes when `pyproject.toml` changes (so a dep bump invalidates\n  the cache) and that a warm run reports a cache hit.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `cache: 'pip'` + `cache-dependency-path: pyproject.toml` set on all dep-installing\n      `setup-python` steps in `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`, `_optionality.yml`,\n      and `.github/workflows/test.yml`.\n- [ ] A repeat run logs a pip cache hit; install time on the cache-hit run is measurably\n      lower than the cold run.\n- [ ] A `pyproject.toml` dependency change invalidates the cache (new key).\n- [ ] Change passes CI (`Verified +1`) and lands via Gerrit.","id":"bad4-7e97-deb4-4eb4","parent_id":"ce0e-f618-a2a4-4ee4","priority":3,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Enable pip caching on all setup-python steps in CI workflows"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783966198522493001,"uuid":"5c3f51ee-0705-4821-acbd-a84014fa6dce"}